{:proof/problem-id "apm-a97A03", :proof/classification :partial, :proof/output "\n\n---\n\nTARGET SANITY CHECK — mentions-problem-objects? ✅ (interval \\([a,b]\\), absolute continuity, Lipschitz constant \\(B\\), a.e. derivative bound \\(C\\)) · avoids-assuming-conclusion? ✅ (the Lean target states an equivalence rather than presuming either side) · meaningful-without-prose? ✅ (encodes a precise analytic equivalence that stands on its own) · notes: captures exactly the two bullet assertions for absolutely continuous functions and records the FTC helper lemma needed for one direction.\n\n```\nPROOF-PLAN.EDN\n{:goal \"Show that an absolutely continuous f : [a,b] → ℝ is Lipschitz iff its a.e. derivative is essentially bounded.\"\n :terms [{:name \"absolute continuity\"\n          :meaning \"f(x)-f(y) = ∫_y^x f'(t) dt for every x,y in [a,b].\"\n          :needed-because \"This lets us convert bounds on f' into bounds on f(x)-f(y).\"}\n         {:name \"difference quotient a.e. derivative control\"\n          :meaning \"For Lipschitz f the limit of difference quotients exists a.e. and stays within the Lipschitz constant.\"\n          :needed-because \"Lipschitz ⇒ bounded derivative requires bounding |(f(x+h)-f(x))/h| by B.\"}\n         {:name \"essential supremum\"\n          :meaning \"|f'| ≤ C almost everywhere gives a uniform bound outside a null set.\"\n          :needed-because \"We need the L^∞-style control to integrate as |f(x)-f(y)| ≤ ∫ C = C|x-y|.\"}]\n :strategy [{:id :s1\n             :formal-dependency \"measure-theoretic differentiability of Lipschitz maps\"\n             :informal-dependency \"Stage 1 proof of Lipschitz ⇒ bounded derivative\"\n             :why-this-now \"Show B-Lipschitz implies |f'| ≤ B a.e. by looking at difference quotients as h→0.\"\n             :lean-target \"lipschitz_has_deriv_bound\"\n             :mathlib-status \"Mathlib has Rademacher’s theorem in this simple 1D setting via a.e. differentiability of AC functions.\"}\n            {:id :s2\n             :formal-dependency \"fundamental theorem of calculus for absolutely continuous functions\"\n             :informal-dependency \"Stage 1 proof of bounded derivative ⇒ Lipschitz\"\n             :why-this-now \"Use f(x)-f(y)=∫ f' to bound by C|x-y| once |f'| ≤ C a.e.\"\n             :lean-target \"ac_of_ae_deriv_bound_is_lipschitz\"\n             :mathlib-status \"Needs existing FTC statement for AC functions.\"}]\n :stage-status {:stage1 :done :stage2 :done :stage3 :in-progress :stage4 :pending}}\n```\n\n```\nFORMAL-ALIGNMENT.EDN\n{:main-claim {:informal-claim \"For an absolutely continuous f : [a,b] → ℝ, being Lipschitz is equivalent to having |f'| bounded almost everywhere.\"\n             :formal-name \"ac_lipschitz_iff_ae_deriv_bound\"\n             :formal-target \"∀ {a b : ℝ} (hab : a ≤ b) {f : ℝ → ℝ},\n  AbsolutelyContinuousOn f (Set.Icc a b) →\n    (∃ B > 0, ∀ {x} (hx : x ∈ Set.Icc a b) {y} (hy : y ∈ Set.Icc a b),\n       |f x - f y| ≤ B * |x - y|)\n    ↔\n    (∃ C > 0, (∀ᵐ x ∂(Measure.restrict volume (Set.Icc a b)), |derivWithin f (Set.Icc a b) x| ≤ C)).\"\n             :sanity-check {:mentions-problem-objects? true\n                            :avoids-assuming-conclusion? true\n                            :meaningful-without-prose? true\n                            :notes \"Exactly states the two conditions in the prompt for absolutely continuous functions.\"}}\n :alignments [{:formal-name \"ac_lipschitz_iff_ae_deriv_bound\"\n              :formal-statement \"same as formal-target\"\n              :informal-clause \"Certifies the equivalence of the two bullet conditions.\"\n              :role :main-theorem}\n             {:formal-name \"absCont_ftc_interval\"\n              :formal-statement \"AbsolutelyContinuousOn f (Icc a b) → f y - f x = ∫_{x}^{y} derivWithin f (Icc a b).\"\n              :informal-clause \"Used in the direction bounded derivative ⇒ Lipschitz.\"\n              :role :helper-lemma}]}\n```\n\n---\n\nAll frame artifacts have been populated:\n\n- `execute.md` now contains the full reader-facing solution, lemma dependency discussion, Lean-status report, and Stage 4 revision notes.\n- `proof-plan.edn` lays out the precise goal, key terms, strategies, and stage-status map.\n- `formal-alignment.edn` records the exact Lean statement (`ac_lipschitz_iff_ae_deriv_bound`) plus the FTC helper lemma.\n- `changelog.edn` logs workspace init, Stage 1 and Stage 2 completions, and the Stage 3 blocker (missing Mathlib lemma turning a Lipschitz constant into an a.e. derivative bound).\n\nLean work remains blocked until that bridge lemma is available; once added, the outlined plan can be wired into `Main.lean`.", :proof/extraction {:phases {}, :dependency-graph nil, :arse-questions nil, :classification :partial, :phase-count 0, :dep-graph-count 0, :arse-count 0}, :proof/frame-workspace {:frame/lean-root "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/A97A03/Apm_v2_a97A03_1775003886693", :frame/id "apm-v2-a97A03-1775003886693", :workspace/owner-repo "futon6", :workspace/generated-at "2026-04-01T00:38:06.719777Z", :frame/shared-extension-root "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Local", :frame/module-root "ApmCanaries.Frames.A97A03.Apm_v2_a97A03_1775003886693", :proof/problem-id "a97A03", :workspace/schema "proof-frame-workspace.v1", :frame/workspace-root "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a97A03/apm-v2-a97A03-1775003886693", :artifacts {:proof-plan "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a97A03/apm-v2-a97A03-1775003886693/proof-plan.edn", :formal-alignment "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a97A03/apm-v2-a97A03-1775003886693/formal-alignment.edn", :changelog "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a97A03/apm-v2-a97A03-1775003886693/changelog.edn", :execute-notes "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a97A03/apm-v2-a97A03-1775003886693/execute.md", :workspace-readme "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a97A03/apm-v2-a97A03-1775003886693/README.md", :workspace-metadata 